      <abstract>
        <p>Roundup of recent advertising account changes (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Callaway Golf, Carlsbad, Calif., dismissed its creative agency of seven years, Dailey &amp; Associates, West Hollywood, Calif., and began a review for the assignment, with billings estimated at $40 million. Five agencies are taking part but Calloway declined to identify them. Dailey, part of the Interpublic Group of Companies, continues to handle media planning and buying.</p>
      </block>
